{"id":"path-tracer-52ip","title":"PHYSICS: Volumetric GR renderer uses abs(dl) instead of proper length element","description":"src/GR/render.jl:205 — dl_proper = abs(dl). For null geodesics, proper distance is zero. The correct spatial integration measure is sqrt(|g_{ij} dx^i dx^j|) which accounts for metric curvature.

abs(dl) underestimates proper length near ISCO (where g_rr diverges) and overestimates tangentially. Causes ~10-30% intensity error near ISCO.

Acceptable for visualization. For physics accuracy: dl_proper = sqrt(abs(sum(g[i,j]*dx[i]*dx[j] for i in 2:4, j in 2:4)))","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-12T20:55:11Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-12T20:55:11Z"}

{"id":"path-tracer-c6jb","title":"PERF: GR integrator stepper dispatches on Symbol instead of type","description":"src/GR/integrator.jl:210-213 — _do_step dispatches on stepper::Symbol with a ternary:

stepper === :rk4 ? rk4_step(...) : verlet_step(...)

This prevents the compiler from specializing/inlining. Both code paths exist at runtime.

Fix: Use type parameters:
struct RK4Stepper end
struct VerletStepper end
struct IntegratorConfig{S<:AbstractStepper} ... stepper::S ... end
@inline _do_step(m, x, p, dl, ::RK4Stepper) = rk4_step(m, x, p, dl)
@inline _do_step(m, x, p, dl, ::VerletStepper) = verlet_step(m, x, p, dl)

Eliminates branch entirely, enables inlining. Also extensible for future steppers (e.g., Yoshida symplectic).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-12T20:53:12Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-12T20:53:12Z"}

{"id":"path-tracer-qt4m","title":"TYPE: Scene lights field is type-unstable Vector{AbstractLight}","description":"src/Scene.jl:149 — Scene stores lights::Vector{AbstractLight}, forcing dynamic dispatch on every light access in the render loop.

Fix: Parameterize the lights field:
struct Scene{V, L}
    camera::Camera
    lights::L  # Tuple{DirectionalLight} or Vector{AbstractLight}
    volumes::V
    background::SVec3d
end

For single-light scenes (common case), Tuple{DirectionalLight} gives full specialization. Multi-light mixed-type scenes keep Vector{AbstractLight}.

Estimated: 5-15% overhead reduction for multi-light scenes.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-12T20:53:45Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-12T20:53:45Z"}

{"id":"path-tracer-fwkp","title":"PERF: Missing @fastmath in GR integrator inner loops","description":"src/GR/integrator.jl:78-102 (rk4_step), src/GR/render.jl:155-249 (volumetric trace) — IEEE-754 strict arithmetic by default. For rendering (not exact simulation), @fastmath enables FMA, reassociation, and NaN check elimination.

Fix: Add @fastmath to rk4_step, verlet_step, and volumetric trace functions. NOT to test/validation code.

