{"id":"path-tracer-ns5d","title":"TYPE: RootNode table uses Union-typed Dict, forces type check per access","description":"src/TreeTypes.jl:108 — RootNode stores:
table::Dict{Coord, Union{InternalNode2{T}, Tile{T}}}

Every get_value call hits the Union, penalizing the common case (InternalNode2).

Fix: Separate tiles from children:
struct RootNode{T}
    background::T
    children::Dict{Coord, InternalNode2{T}}
    tiles::Dict{Coord, Tile{T}}
end

Eliminates Union entirely. Root lookup becomes two Dict lookups (children first, then tiles) but both are type-stable.

Impact: Medium for direct tree access via ValueAccessor. NanoVDB bypasses this entirely.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"tobias.osborne@itp.uni-hannover.de","created_at":"2026-03-12T20:53:50Z","created_by":"tobiasosborne","updated_at":"2026-03-12T20:53:50Z"}
